    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="234"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of Staff, United States Army</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marshall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Military Mission in the
                        Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Deane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <gloss target="#t_Octagon1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Octagon</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-14">14 September
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Octagon1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Octagon</hi>
                    </gloss> 26 <gloss target="#t_TopSec1">TopSec</gloss> sent to Deane from
                    Marshall information to Spaatz and <gloss target="#t_AGWar1">AGWar</gloss>.</p>
                <p>If arrangements, satisfactory to Spaatz, reference your <gloss target="#t_MX1"
                        >MX</gloss> 20947 of 13 September<note n="1" xml:id="d234fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_404">p. 404</ref>.</note> and
                    further reference our <gloss target="#t_Octagon1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Octagon</hi>
                    </gloss> 10,<note n="2" xml:id="d234fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_397">p. 397</ref>.</note>
                    Russians and <pb facs="0468" n="406" xml:id="pg_406"/> yourself, can be
                    completed without representatives from London proceeding to Moscow it is
                    satisfactory here. You and Spaatz complete the arrangements and carry out the
                    project as the two of you see fit.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
